h3. Issue Summary

The Jira [REST API documentation |https://developer.atlassian.com/server/jira/platform/rest/v11002/intro/#pagination]contains incorrect parameters in the example REST call for pagination, which limits the response size for resources. 
h3. Expected Results

The pagination request mentioned in the [REST API documentation|https://developer.atlassian.com/server/jira/platform/rest/v11002/intro/#pagination] should contain the *startAt* and *maxResults* parameters to retrieve the first item in the results and define the maximum number of results returned per page. The corrected request should be as below :
{code:java}
Request 

http://host:port/context/rest/api-name/api-version/resource-name?startAt=0&maxResults=10 {code}
h3. Actual Results

The request in the REST API documentation contains *start* and *limit* parameters for pagination.
{code:java}
Request 

http://host:port/context/rest/api-name/api-version/resource-name?start=0&limit=10{code}
h3. Steps to Reproduce

NA
h3. Workaround

Use *startAt* and *maxResults* parameters in the Jira REST API calls for pagination.
{code:java}
http://host:port/context/rest/api-name/api-version/resource-name?startAt=0&maxResults=10  {code}

Currently, updating the assignee field on an issue triggers an 'Issue Updated' event, which may activate unnecessary hooks. Since there is already an 'issue_assigned' event, it would be better to keep just the 'issue_assigned' event or the 'issue_updated' event, similar to how it was in Jira 9 and earlier. 

Example: 

First Payload : 
{code:java}
{
  "timestamp": 1762780415913,
  "webhookEvent": "jira:issue_updated",
  "issue_event_type_name": "issue_assigned",
{code}
Second Payload: 
 
{code:java}
{
  "timestamp": 1762780415913,
  "webhookEvent": "jira:issue_updated",
  "issue_event_type_name": "issue_updated",
  "user": { {code}
In Jira 9 and earlier, only the issue_updated event is triggered, not the issue_assigned. 

From the following documentation we see that this is the default behavior : 

[https://developer.atlassian.com/platform/forge/events-reference/jira/?tabId=4&tab=payload#issue-assigned]
{quote}Issue assigned
An event with the name avi:jira:assigned:issue is sent when a user is assigned or unassigned from an issue. An "issue updated" event will also be sent when this occurs.
{quote}
